{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T09:03:02.818Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Adam & AdamW — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Adam & AdamW Are"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam (Adaptive Moment Estimation)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the most popular optimizer in deep learning, combining "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Momentum"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (first moment) and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "RMSProp"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (second moment) to enable faster convergence with minimal tuning."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW (Adam with Weight Decay)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a corrected variant of Adam that "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "decouples weight decay from the learning rate update"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", leading to more effective regularization and better generalization."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AdamW is the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "non-negotiable default"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for training transformers, LLMs, and large-scale neural networks in 2025 and beyond, with most LLMs now trained with AdamW instead of standard Adam."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Adam & AdamW Matter in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Preferred Optimizer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reason"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transformers/LLMs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AdamW"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard for state-of-the-art models"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Diffusion models"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AdamW"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Better stability, less overfitting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "StyleGAN"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AdamW"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prevents mode collapse, better generalization"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "YOLO object detection"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adam"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Combines momentum + RMSProp effectively"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "General deep learning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adam"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Minimal tuning, robust convergence"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adam revolutionized deep learning by computing individual adaptive learning rates for different parameters, allowing neural networks to converge significantly faster than traditional methods."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Adam Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Two Historical Buffers"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adam maintains "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "two historical buffers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for every parameter:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Momentum (First Moment)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Tracks moving average of past gradients to maintain velocity"}]}]}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance (Second Moment)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Tracks moving average of squared gradients to scale learning rate"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Update Formulas"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "First moment (momentum)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nm_t = \\beta_1 \\times m"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{t-1} + (1 - \\beta_1) \\times g_t\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Second moment (variance)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nv_t = \\beta_2 \\times v"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{t-1} + (1 - \\beta_2) \\times g_t^2\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bias correction"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (for cold start):\n\\[\n\\hat{m}"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "t = \\frac{m_t}{1 - \\beta_1^t}\n\\]\n\\[\n\\hat{v}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "t = \\frac{v_t}{1 - \\beta_2^t}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameter update"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\n\\theta"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{t+1} = \\theta_t - \\frac{\\eta}{\\sqrt{\\hat{v}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "t} + \\epsilon} \\times \\hat{m}"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "t\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "g_t"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Gradient at time step t\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\beta_1, \\beta_2"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Decay rates (typically 0.9, 0.999)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\eta"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Learning rate (typically 0.001)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\epsilon"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Epsilon for numerical stability (1e-8)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Features"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effect"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Larger steps in flat areas"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Accelerates through low-gradient regions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Smaller steps in steep/noisy areas"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dampens oscillations"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Individual learning rates per parameter"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adapts to each weight's gradient history"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Minimal tuning required"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Default values work well for most models"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This combination allows taking larger steps in flat areas and smaller, more cautious steps in steep or noisy areas."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How AdamW Fixes Adam"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Problem with Adam + L2 Regularization"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Standard Adam"}, {"type": "text", "text": " applies weight decay (L2 regularization) to the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "learning rate itself"}, {"type": "text", "text": " before updating parameters:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Adam's L2 regularization (WRONG)\ngrad = grad.add(param, alpha=weight_decay)  # Adds to gradient [web:156]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem: Weight decay interferes with Adam's adaptive learning rate mechanism because the regularization term is in the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "numerator and denominator"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of the gradient update, minimizing its effect."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": L2 regularization cannot act as proper weight decay in Adam."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AdamW's Solution: Decoupled Weight Decay"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW"}, {"type": "text", "text": " decouples weight decay from gradient update, applying it "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "directly to parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": " after the Adam update:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# AdamW's weight decay (CORRECT)\nparam.mul_(1 - lr * weight_decay)  # Subtracts from parameter [web:156]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This subtracts a fraction of the weights directly during the weight update step."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Update Formula Difference"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optimizer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight Decay Application"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{grad} = \\text{grad} + \\text{wd} \\times w"}}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "w = w - \\text{lr} \\times \\text{wd} \\times w"}}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW follows the second equation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", decoupling weight decay from gradient-based updates."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Differences: Adam vs. AdamW"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adam"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AdamW"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weight decay"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Added to gradient (L2 regularization)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Subtracted from parameter (decoupled)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regularization effect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Interferes with adaptive LR"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Applied uniformly across layers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Generalization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Better (less overfitting)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convergence"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Faster with weight decay"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transformers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Less common"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Default"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "lr=0.001, no wd"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "lr=0.001, wd=0.01"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why AdamW is Better (Mathematical Insight)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "standard gradient descent"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", L2 regularization and weight decay are equivalent:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{regularized loss} = \\text{loss} + \\frac{\\text{L2 term}}{}"}}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "w = w - \\text{lr} \\times w.\\text{grad} - \\text{lr} \\times \\text{wd} \\times w"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "But in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", they become different because:\n- L2 regularization is added to gradient (first equation)\n- The regularization term is in the adaptive LR denominator"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW"}, {"type": "text", "text": " uses the second equation (proper weight decay), so it acts as true weight decay rather than being neutralized by adaptive LR."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adam & AdamW in PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard Adam"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\nimport torch.optim as optim\n\nmodel = torch.nn.Linear(10, 1)\n\n# Adam optimizer\noptimizer = optim.Adam(\n    model.parameters(),\n    lr=0.001,        # Learning rate [web:154]\n    betas=(0.9, 0.999),  # β₁, β₂ [web:154]\n    eps=1e-8         # Epsilon [web:154]\n)\n\n# With L2 regularization (not recommended)\noptimizer = optim.Adam(\n    model.parameters(),\n    lr=0.001,\n    weight_decay=0.01  # L2 regularization (interferes with adaptive LR) [web:156]\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AdamW (Recommended)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# AdamW optimizer (non-negotiable default for transformers) [web:130]\noptimizer = optim.AdamW(\n    model.parameters(),\n    lr=0.001,        # Learning rate [web:154]\n    betas=(0.9, 0.999),  # β₁, β₂ [web:154]\n    eps=1e-8,        # Epsilon [web:154]\n    weight_decay=0.01  # Proper weight decay (decoupled) [web:156]\n)\n\n# Training loop\nfor data, target in dataset:\n    output = model(data)\n    loss = torch.nn.MSELoss()(output, target)\n    \n    optimizer.zero_grad()\n    loss.backward()\n    optimizer.step()  # AdamW update with decoupled weight decay"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AdamW in TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tensorflow as tf\n\n# Adam optimizer\noptimizer_adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(\n    learning_rate=0.001,\n    weight_decay=None  # L2 regularization not recommended [web:156]\n)\n\n# AdamW optimizer (recommended default)\noptimizer_adamw = tf.keras.optimizers.AdamW(\n    learning_rate=0.001,\n    weight_decay=0.004  # Default weight decay [web:156]\n)\n\n# Training\nmodel.fit(\n    train_data,\n    train_labels,\n    epochs=100,\n    optimizer=optimizer_adamw  # Use AdamW\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Adam vs. AdamW"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Adam When:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No weight decay needed"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Overfitting is less of concern"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple tasks"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Basic deep learning problems"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Legacy models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Older architectures that used Adam"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use AdamW When:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Using weight decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": You likely should be"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transformers/LLMs"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Standard for state-of-the-art"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Diffusion models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Better stability"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Complex models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Large-scale neural networks"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overfitting concerns"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Need better generalization"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rule of thumb"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": If you're using weight decay (and you likely should be!), "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW is generally the preferred choice"}, {"type": "text", "text": " due to more effective and transparent regularization."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparison with Other Optimizers"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optimizer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Momentum"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adaptive LR"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight Decay"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best Use"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ No"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ No"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Manual"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Computer vision"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Momentum"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ No"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Manual"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Accelerate SGD"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "RMSProp"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ No"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Manual"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "RNNs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "L2 (interferes)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "General deep learning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Decoupled"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformers/LLMs"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam = Momentum + RMSProp"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and is the most superior optimizer that robustly adapts to large datasets and deep networks."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam"}, {"type": "text", "text": " as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "rolling a ball with smart brakes"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Momentum"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Ball builds velocity (accelerates through flat areas)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "RMSProp"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Brakes adjust automatically (smaller steps in steep/noisy areas)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Combined"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Accelerates in flat regions, slows down in steep regions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW"}, {"type": "text", "text": " as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam with proper weight decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam update"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Ball moves based on adaptive LR + momentum"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Decoupled weight decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": After moving, shrink ball slightly (prevent overfitting)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Better regularization, more stable training"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Combines Momentum + RMSProp for adaptive learning rates with momentum"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Adam with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "decoupled weight decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that doesn't interfere with adaptive LR"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Two buffers"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": First moment (momentum) + Second moment (variance)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Update formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\theta_{t+1} = \\theta_t - \\frac{\\eta}{\\sqrt{\\hat{v}_t} + \\epsilon} \\times \\hat{m}_t"}}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bias correction"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\hat{m}_t = \\frac{m_t}{1 - \\beta_1^{t}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\hat{v}_t = \\frac{v_t}{1 - \\beta_2^{t}}"}}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hyperparameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": lr=0.001, β₁=0.9, β₂=0.999, ε=1e-8"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam's bug"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Weight decay added to gradient (interferes with adaptive LR)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW's fix"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Weight decay applied directly to parameters (decoupled)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transformers"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": AdamW is non-negotiable default for 2025"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Most LLMs"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Trained with AdamW instead of Adam"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Better generalization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": AdamW prevents overfitting more effectively"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Faster convergence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": AdamW with weight decay converges faster"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PyTorch"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "optim.AdamW(lr=0.001, weight_decay=0.01)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Minimal tuning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Adam works well with default values"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "RNNs"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": RMSProp often better than Adam"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adam and AdamW are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "powerful tools"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in deep learning, with AdamW being the preferred choice for modern architectures due to its more effective and transparent regularization that leads to improved performance and faster convergence."}]}]}}